HEADWORD: marasca cherry
<hw>marasca cherry</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A Dalmation
bitter wild cherry tree (<spn>Prunus cerasus</spn> <varn>marasca</varn>)
bearing fruit whose juice is made into maraschino liqueur.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> marasca, maraschino cherry.</syn>⟦br⟧
